### üìö Examples of Use

The `examples/` directory contains three complete use cases applying Riemannian STATS to different datasets:

| Dataset        | Description                                                                                                                                                   | Script                                                                                                | Results                                                                          |
| -------------- |---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Iris           | Applies Riemannian PCA to 150 flowers from 3 species using 4 morphological variables (sepal/petal length and width). Visualizes species in component space.   | [üßæ example1.py](https://github.com/OldemarRodriguez/riemannian_stats/blob/main/examples/example1.py) | [üìä View Output](https://riemannianstats.web.app/_static/examples/Example1.html) |
| Data10D\_250   | Synthetic dataset with 250 points in 10 dimensions and labeled clusters. Computes UMAP similarities, rho matrix, R-PCA, and correlation analysis.             | [üßæ example2.py](https://github.com/OldemarRodriguez/riemannian_stats/blob/main/examples/example2.py) | [üìä View Output](https://riemannianstats.web.app/_static/examples/Example2.html) |
| Olivetti Faces | 400 grayscale face images (64√ó64 pixels, 4096D) from 40 individuals. Projects them into Riemannian component space for identity separation and visualization. | [üßæ example3.py](https://github.com/OldemarRodriguez/riemannian_stats/blob/main/examples/example3.py) | [üìä View Output](https://riemannianstats.web.app/_static/examples/Example3.html) |


üìñ For full walkthroughs with inputs, outputs, and visualizations:
[üìä Examples Overview](https://riemannianstats.web.app/examples.html)

